                          <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="true" xml:id="binding">
                              <decoNote xml:id="b1">The book is sewn on four sewing stations (two pairs) linked to uncovered wooden boards.</decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                        </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Boards">
                              The left board is broken in three parts and the right board is broken in two. The parts are held together by leather strings and threads of vegetal origin.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Cover">
                              On the boards there are traces of leather turn-ins.</decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b5" type="Endbands">
                                A row of small holes is present on head and tail of the spine.
                                They might be traces of the attachment of the endbands or the holes used for the quire tackets.
                                In the 3rd quire the thread used for the tacket or for sewing the endband is still present.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b6" type="SewingStations">4</decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b7">
                              The sewing is a chain-stitch on four sewing stations (two pairs). The sewing follows the <term key="patternA" ana="#patternA">pattern A</term> by Bozzacchi.
                              The thread used for the sewing is of <term key="vegetalThread" ana="#vegetalThread">vegetal origin.</term>
                              </decoNote>
                            </binding>
                          </bindingDesc>
                        </physDesc>



